children.text: Cough is a natural bodily function to assist in clearing materials from the airways and prevent them from going into the lungs.
⦁ Thick green or yellow or blood sputum
Cough is the most common symptom in primary care settings. According to the time cough is divided in to acute cough, Subacute cough and chronic cough

⦁ Acute cough: refers to cough within 3 weeks, which is the most common symptom in respiratory disease. Causes include cold, acute bronchitis, pneumonia, respiratory infections, tuberculosis, and foreign bodies in tracheal ect.
⦁ subacute cough: duration of more than 3 weeks, within 8 weeks of cough called subacute cough, the reasons are more complex, often self-limiting

⦁ chronic cough: lasts more than 8 weeks, can last for several years or even for decades. The causes including cough variant asthma (allergic bronchitis), upper respiratory cough syndrome (allergic rhino-bronchitis), gastroesophageal reflux, chronic bronchitis, etc. Among them, cough variant asthma and upper respiratory cough syndrome are the most common.
If Cough is interfering with your daily life, log on AITMED and talk to a doctor to receive a treatment plan customized for you.
